{
  "body": "There was an [attempt](https://github.com/perl6/doc/commit/38ed8fbc7f1005db4cea683bb8dad3324da196ac) to recommend ``«»`` which was then [reverted](https://github.com/perl6/doc/commit/a8b908539d9999f0cc17dbc8a57da83909e6e013). This resulted in a [discussion](https://irclog.perlgeek.de/perl6/2018-01-23#i_15728317) in which a better alternative was suggested (``< >``).\r\n\r\nI think the docs should talk about that too.\r\n\r\nSo I'm suggesting this:\r\n```perl6\r\nrun ‘rm’, ‘--’, $file; # ← we currently show something like this\r\nrun <rm -->, $file;    # ← this should be recommended as an alternative\r\nrun «rm -- \"$file\"»;   # ← this should be discussed, and likely discouraged (with examples on why it is potentially dangerous)\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
